                        <p>Neurological research conducted at the University of California in 2023 found that listening to ocean sounds for just 20 minutes reduced insomnia symptoms by up to 40% in study participants. Additionally, the negative ions present in sea air have been linked to increased serotonin production, helping alleviate symptoms of depression and seasonal affective disorder.</p>

